1. Running pip as a module
    pip install ... do not specify the version of python
    Python(version) -m pip install ... remove the ambiguity
    
2. Create and active venv in Window
    Python -m venv venv
    venv\Scripts\activate
    deactivate
    
3. Reinstall pip
    Python -m ensurepip --upgrade
    or  Python get-pip.py 
    
4. install multiple packages in a single line
   install from specific URL
   insta

5. pip list, show version (__version__)

6. show package dependency
    Python -m pip show requests   then show dependency for each dependent packages before uninstall

7. Uninstall
    Python -m pip uninstall urllib3 -y
    python -m pip uninstall -y charset-normalizer idna requests
    
8. Requirement file
    Python -m pip freeze > requirements.txt
    Python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
    ==, >= , < version
    
9. Seperate dev and production
    python -m pip install -r requirements_dev.txt
    -r requirements.txt \n    pytest>=x.y.z   # requirements_dev.txt
    Python -m pip install -r requirements.txt

10. venv and virtualev

11. A python virtual environment is a folder structure
